{
  "stem": "1033.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know, the first things in Montreal when I came-- when we left-- George and I left Glace Bay and came to Montreal.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And both of us started working in the clothing trade.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there were-- there were a lot of French Canadians in that trade, working alongside us.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And one of the marvelous, uplifting, astounding discoveries I made-- that the French Roman Catholics were also circumcised.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because that-- you know, as a Jewish boy in Europe, you, you, you, you didn't have a chance if you were circumcised.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the very first thing I, I felt-- I'm safe.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There's other kids who are circumcised, people like myself.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they're not Jewish.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It's just an aside.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Now, I don't know to what extent I have answered your question in terms of relevance to what people thought about the war.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We tried to forget about the war.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "There is something in, in human nature-- there is certainly something in my own nature-- and I would say it's a good aspect-- that it tries to look for the lark aspect, the, the fun, the bizarre, the, the joyous.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The macabre goes nowhere.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And, and having survived what I had survived personally-- and I can really only speak of myself-- I knew that that kind of thinking is a dead end.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I often speculated and wondered about my own mother.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Because I, I, I am 64 years old.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I still feel ripped off.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I didn't have someone who, as a child, who had me in her arms.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And it's-- it-- it's, it's kind of lurid for me to speak of this right now.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But I thought that if my mom hadn't been so terrified-- if, if she-- a sense of humor is so wonderful.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I mean terror, I am sure-- Hitler did not invent terror.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Human existence had always entailed an undesirable or, or worse aspect.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And people have always had to make the best of where they were, who they were, and where they hoped to go.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So, so I, I-- I looked for the-- if not for the positive, then, then for the humorous.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, and even though I had told you a dreadful tale which happened to me, there were heartening aspects of it.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Like the guard giving me-- I am me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I only know me.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I may be looking at you and looking even at my kids.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But really, I have a glancing acquaintance with myself and less with others, even though observation does help for us to kind of position ourselves in terms of the rest of humankind.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I find that, that-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the war, in many ways, apart from being a personal pain, is a giant embarrassment to me.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I feel really embarrassed for the Germans-- for people, for people.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I always looked at the guards.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I even looked at Mengele as an extension of myself.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And, and there are a couple of things.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It's really a fantasy.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But I will tell you, for whatever it's worth.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "My, my grandfather's mother was the daughter of the very famous Rabbi Jungreis.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It's a well-known, very religious, even today, Orthodox Jewish family.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And there are some rabbis today by the name of Jungreis.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I just wondered if somehow, maybe his godliness and his goodness, through his genes, I had inherited something that will survive.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And what-- how that connects to the concept of God, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I wouldn't spend too much time trying to identify it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] What-- the other thing is that, that taking that as, as part of me, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] when I look out through my eyes, I see people.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I assume that they're very much like myself.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Like-- and perhaps because of my unusual deprivation at birth of a father, I, I, I, I had a-- an, an inordinate tendency to, to look for affection, to look for love from others.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And when you take that beyond, to give what I didn't have.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And in that sense, I have a chance to understand myself.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "In terms of thinking about the war and what people thought of the war then, I have always been profoundly grateful for the Jews who put in their $5 and $10 and $20 to the Congress, who made it possible that hundreds of us kids could come and start a new life and let new roots.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And, and-- so that there is a tomorrow for us and an opportunity to continue to be, to continue to give-- which, per force of our natures, we must give.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Anything that one doesn't give, one doesn't have.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
